        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Cook the soup",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat {{extra-virgin-olive-oil}} of oil in a large saucepan over a medium heat. Add the {{onion}} onion and {{carrot}} carrot and cook for 6 minutes until soft. Add the {{garlic}} of garlic, {{cumin-ground}} of cumin, and {{smoked-paprika}} of paprika and cook for 1 minute. Add {{tomato-puree}} of tomato purée and cook for 30 seconds.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the {{lentils-red}} of rinsed red lentils and pour in {{stock-vegetable}} of hot stock. Bring to a simmer and cook for 20 minutes until the lentils have dissolved completely.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Blend until smooth. Taste and season with salt. If too thick, thin with a little hot water.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Make the paprika butter and serve",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Melt {{unsalted-butter}} of butter in a small pan over a medium heat until it begins to foam. Add {{smoked-paprika}} of paprika and {{mint-dried}} of dried mint. Swirl the pan ,  the butter should sizzle and turn vivid red. Take off the heat immediately.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Ladle the soup into bowls. Pour a spoonful of hot paprika butter over each bowl. Serve with lemon wedges alongside.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Have the bowls ready before starting the butter. Once paprika is in, the heat from the butter alone is enough. Take the pan off the heat after 15 seconds and pour immediately.",
                "cause": "The butter was left on the heat too long after the paprika was added.",
                "symptom": "Paprika butter is burnt and bitter"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Start with 900 ml of stock and add more after blending if needed. The soup should be thick enough to coat the back of a spoon.",
                "cause": "Too much stock for the volume of lentils.",
                "symptom": "Soup is too thin"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Red lentils should dissolve completely at a gentle simmer within 20 minutes. If still grainy at 20 minutes, increase heat slightly and cook for another 10.",
                "cause": "Very old lentils, or the simmer was too gentle.",
                "symptom": "Lentils are gritty after 20 minutes"
              },
              {
                "fix": "The lemon wedge is not optional here. A squeeze of lemon over the bowl transforms the soup. Season generously with salt and taste again.",
                "cause": "Insufficient seasoning, or lemon not served alongside.",
                "symptom": "Soup tastes flat"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Mercimek çorbasi is served in every Turkish restaurant and on family tables year-round. It is the soup made when the kitchen is nearly empty, and the soup that begins a proper dinner. The spice blend varies by region. In the southeast it is spicier; in Istanbul it tends to be smoother and thinner.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
